dReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9305.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> Darn, and here I thought I might have the ONLY pair.  They're an insanely rare drop in Tenebrous.  (After killing 70 or so of the same 3-4 named mobs... a cleric friend of mine had these drop).<br><br>The effect is vampiric embrace.  Gloves must be worn to use them.  It's a right click self-only buff based on the Necromancer version of the spell.  At lvl 59 it gave me a 71point lifetap proc (in addition to what my weapons already do), at lvl 60, it's a 72 point lifetap proc.  I don't know the minimum level to use... but it's been reported at 25.  Casting time is about 6 seconds.<br><br>At first glance, it's not all the great of an item... but I can assure you after using them for about a month now... they're friggin AMAZING!  I taunt like it's nobody's business, the proc happens more often that my epic weapon procs.  Combined with 2 bloodpoints, I can fight light-blue mobs... non-stop... and always be at full health.  There's nothing I'd love more than to never see this item posted publicly (so that verant won't come around and nerf it).<br><br>If these drop, and a warrior is in the group.  They should get them based on &quot;need based&quot; rules.  The stats aren't overly impressive... but the effect is.<br><br>Estimated Value: 15k (easily)<br>What I'd recommend paying: up to 45k <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukalran.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalran</A> at: 1/2/02 2:09:08 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=remfdatroll>Remf da Troll</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/2/02 2:15:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9305.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> info please?</span><hr size=1> Okay, feed a starving warrior- did they drop off the vampires in the castle (i.e. the winged ones) or the lower level named ones in the camps around the zone?   I'm guessing the castle, but verification would be greatly appreciated! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>RdT. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utabbran.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tabbran</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/2/02 2:38:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9305.topic&index=13>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: info please?</span><hr size=1> Winged vamp guys in the castle ;)<br><br>They have lots of random drops, and some rare loots that are fairly amazing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uxuilidar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xuilidar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/2/02 2:58:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9305.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top ali